bib_record.title: Thick-target yields and astrophysical thermonuclear reaction rates: proton-induced reactions

free_txt: University of Colorado variable
energy cyclotron facility.
Ge(Li) detector, shielded by approximately 20
cm of lead on all sides to detect beta-delayed decay
gammas or annihilation quanta. Detector calibration
results: energy is within  3 keV and efficiency is
within 5%.
University of Colorado variable
energy cyclotron facility.
Data on
30 reaction yields that are published in J,AND,23,177,
197902 and missing in this entry.
Targets were sufficiently thick to stop the beam, and
assumed to be isotopically pure.

velocity, averaged over the Maxwell-Boltzmann
velocity distribution at the temperature T of interest.
